events.originalText: A general strike began in Guinea as an attempt to force President Lansana Conté to resign, eventually resulting in the appointment of two new prime ministers.
events.subtitle: 2007 Guinean general strike
events.headline: General strike in Guinea leads to appointment of two new prime ministers

events.originalText: The Braer Storm, the strongest extratropical cyclone ever recorded in the North Atlantic, reached peak intensity.
events.subtitle: Braer Storm
events.headline: Braer Storm reaches peak intensity in North Atlantic

events.originalText: Sir Clive Sinclair launched the Sinclair C5 personal electric vehicle, "one of the great marketing bombs of postwar British industry", which later became a cult collectable despite its commercial failure.
events.subtitle: Clive Sinclair
events.headline: Sir Clive Sinclair launches cult collectable electric vehicle

events.originalText: India and Pakistan signed the Tashkent Declaration to end the Indo-Pakistani war of 1965.
events.subtitle: Tashkent Declaration
events.headline: India and Pakistan sign Tashkent Declaration to end war

events.originalText: The first session of the United Nations General Assembly convened at the Methodist Central Hall in London with representatives from 51 member states.
events.subtitle: United Nations General Assembly
events.headline: First session of UN General Assembly convenes in London

events.originalText: Greco-Italian War: The Greek army captured the strategically important Klisura Pass in Albania.
events.subtitle: Greco-Italian War
events.headline: Greek army captures Klisura Pass in Albania

events.originalText: Tintin in the Land of the Soviets, the first volume of The Adventures of Tintin by the Belgian cartoonist Hergé, began serialisation.
events.subtitle: Tintin in the Land of the Soviets
events.headline: Tintin in the Land of the Soviets begins serialisation

events.originalText: The science fiction film Metropolis, directed by Fritz Lang, was released in Germany.
events.subtitle: Science fiction
events.headline: Metropolis film released in Germany

events.originalText: Lithuanian residents of the Klaipėda Region began a revolt, ahead of a League of Nations decision on their future which they expected to be against their interest.
events.subtitle: Klaipėda Region
events.headline: Lithuanian residents revolt ahead of League of Nations decision

events.originalText: Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition: Seven survivors of the Ross Sea party were rescued after being stranded for several months.
events.subtitle: Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition
events.headline: Seven survivors rescued in Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition

events.originalText: The first great gusher of the Texas oil boom was discovered in the Spindletop oil field near Beaumont.
events.subtitle: Blowout (well drilling)
events.headline: First great gusher discovered in Texas oil boom

events.originalText: Service began on the Metropolitan Railway (construction depicted) between Paddington and Farringdon Street, today the oldest segment of the London Underground.
events.subtitle: Metropolitan Railway
events.headline: Service begins on Metropolitan Railway in London Underground

events.originalText: New Orleans (pictured), the first steamship on the Mississippi River, arrived at New Orleans to complete its maiden voyage.
events.subtitle: New Orleans (steamboat)
events.headline: New Orleans steamship completes maiden voyage on Mississippi River

events.originalText: Common Sense, a pamphlet by Thomas Paine denouncing British rule in the Thirteen Colonies, was published.
events.subtitle: Common Sense
events.headline: Common Sense pamphlet denouncing British rule published

events.originalText: Moldavian–Ottoman Wars: Stephen the Great led Moldavian forces to defeat an Ottoman attack under Hadım Suleiman Pasha near Vaslui in present-day Romania.
events.subtitle: Moldavian–Ottoman Wars
events.headline: Moldavian forces defeat Ottoman attack near Vaslui

events.originalText: Philip the Good established the Order of the Golden Fleece, referred to as the most prestigious, exclusive, and expensive order of chivalry in the world.
events.subtitle: Philip the Good
events.headline: Philip the Good establishes prestigious Order of the Golden Fleece

events.originalText: After the death of his guardian John I Tzimiskes, Basil II became the effective ruler and senior emperor of the Byzantine Empire.
events.subtitle: John I Tzimiskes
events.headline: Basil II becomes ruler of Byzantine Empire

events.originalText: Pope Fabian, said to have been chosen by the Holy Spirit when a dove landed on his head, began his papacy.
events.subtitle: Pope Fabian
events.headline: Pope Fabian begins papacy after dove lands on his head

events.originalText: The Western Han dynasty of China ended after the throne was usurped by Wang Mang, who founded the Xin dynasty.
events.subtitle: AD 9
events.headline: Western Han dynasty ends as Wang Mang founds Xin dynasty
